  <span id="freeText11888607128752983410" style="display:none">This book proves that Frank Peretti is the Stephen King of Christian fiction. I think I read this one in about a day and a night. I was worthless for the whole time I was reading it because I couldn't put it down. I read it while my husband was away on a business trip and then I wouldn't put it down until I finished it because my imagination about what might happen next creeped me out more than continuing to read it. So I read it until moving into the larger of the wee hours of the morning. All the while, with every turn of the page I wanted to scream at the characters, "No!!! Don't go there!" But they did.</span>
