<span id="freeTextContainer7472247936355354641">I love this book. I read it many years ago right after it first came out, but for me it remains the quintessential classic Christian fiction. Peretti&apos;s dragon is a great analogy for how sin blends in around us and works almost unseen until it devours us.<br/><br/>In my opinion this book is Frank Peretti&apos;s best work--and I have read a lot of his books. Great storytelling with a great message. </span>
  <span id="freeText7472247936355354641" style="display:none">I love this book. I read it many years ago right after it first came out, but for me it remains the quintessential classic Christian fiction. Peretti's dragon is a great analogy for how sin blends in around us and works almost unseen until it devours us.<br /><br />In my opinion this book is Frank Peretti's best work--and I have read a lot of his books. Great storytelling with a great message. </span>
